    "articles": {
      "demo-article-install": {
        "title": "Install the Wexio widget on your site",
        "excerpt": "A 30-second snippet you paste before the closing </body> tag.",
        "body": "## Add the loader script\n\nPaste this snippet into every page where you want the widget to appear:\n\n```html\n<script\n  src=\"https://cdn.wexio.io/loader.js\"\n  data-public-key=\"pk_live_YOUR_KEY\"\n></script>\n```\n\nThe loader injects a floating launcher in the bottom-right corner. Click it to open the chat panel.\n\n## Verify the install\n\n- Visit a page that includes the snippet.\n- Open the browser console.\n- You should see `[wexio] widget mounted`.\n\n## Customise the look\n\nThe widget reads brand colours from your dashboard. Update them in **Settings → Brand**.\n\n> Need a hand? Tap \"Still need help? Message us\" below and we'll walk you through it."
      },
      "demo-article-flows": {
        "title": "Build your first automation flow",
        "excerpt": "Drag, drop, and ship a welcome bot in under five minutes.",
        "body": "## What's a flow?\n\nA flow is a tiny tree of conversation steps - questions, replies, and conditions - that runs whenever a visitor matches a trigger.\n\n## Three trigger types\n\n1. **Visitor opened the widget** - greet first-timers.\n2. **Visitor asked a question** - Gaia (AI) tries to answer; if it can't, the flow takes over.\n3. **Webhook received** - your CMS or e-commerce platform pushes an event; the flow kicks off in the right chat.\n\n## Best practices\n\n- Keep first replies under 80 characters.\n- Offer 2-3 quick-reply chips, not a free-text question.\n- Always provide an escape hatch - *\"Talk to a human\"*."
      },
      "demo-article-slack": {
        "title": "Forward chats to Slack",
        "excerpt": "Mirror every new conversation into a Slack channel of your choice.",
        "body": "## Connect your workspace\n\nIn **Integrations → Slack** click *Connect*. You'll be redirected to Slack's OAuth screen - approve the requested scopes (`chat:write`, `channels:read`).\n\n## Pick a channel\n\nAfter authorising, choose the target channel (or create a new one like `#support`).\n\n## What gets forwarded\n\n- The opening message, with a deeplink back to the wexio inbox.\n- Operator replies as threaded messages.\n- Visitor replies in real time via the SSE bridge.\n\n## Reverse direction\n\nOperators can reply *from* Slack - wexio listens for Slack thread replies and posts them back to the widget."
      },
      "demo-article-billing": {
        "title": "Update your plan and billing details",
        "excerpt": "Switch tiers, change card, or download invoices.",
        "body": "## Plans\n\n- **Free** - 1 widget, basic features, \"Powered by Wexio\" badge.\n- **Standard** - unlimited widgets, automations, integrations.\n- **Enterprise** - white-label, SLA, dedicated support.\n\n## Change plan\n\n**Settings → Billing → Change plan**. Upgrades take effect immediately; downgrades apply at the end of the current cycle.\n\n## Invoices\n\nDownload every invoice as PDF from **Billing → History**. We also email a copy on each renewal."
      },
      "demo-article-theme": {
        "title": "Customise the widget theme",
        "excerpt": "Match the widget to your brand - colours, radii, dark mode.",
        "body": "## Brand colours\n\nIn **Settings → Brand**, set:\n\n- **Primary** - drives the launcher, send button, focus rings.\n- **Background** - the panel surface (light) and dark-mode pair.\n\n## Radii\n\nPick from `sm`, `md`, `lg` for a tighter or softer look. The change applies live to every widget on every page.\n\n## Dark mode\n\nDefault = follow the visitor's system preference. Pin to **always light** or **always dark** if your site doesn't support dark mode itself."
      },
      "demo-article-handoff": {
        "title": "Hand off from Gaia to a human operator",
        "excerpt": "When AI isn't enough - route the visitor to a teammate.",
        "body": "## Triggers\n\nGaia hands off automatically when:\n\n- The visitor types *\"talk to a human\"* (or any localised variant).\n- The same question is asked twice with no resolution.\n- The visitor's intent matches a routing rule (e.g., billing → finance team).\n\n## Routing\n\nSet up **Routing → Rules** to direct certain intents to specific teams or operators. Round-robin and least-loaded are both supported.\n\n## Out-of-hours\n\nIf no operator is online, Gaia offers a callback or email-handoff form instead of pretending someone's available."
      },
      "demo-article-crm": {
        "title": "Sync conversations to your CRM",
        "excerpt": "Push every chat into HubSpot, Salesforce, or Pipedrive.",
        "body": "## Supported CRMs\n\n- HubSpot (OAuth)\n- Salesforce (OAuth)\n- Pipedrive (API token)\n- Custom via webhooks\n\n## What syncs\n\n- New conversations create a contact (if not already present) and a note.\n- Operator replies append to the contact timeline.\n- Tags applied in wexio mirror to the CRM.\n\n## Two-way\n\nOperator notes added in the CRM can post back to wexio via the webhook receiver - see *Integrations → Webhooks → Inbound*."
      },
      "demo-article-shortcuts": {
        "title": "Operator keyboard shortcuts",
        "excerpt": "Triage twice as fast - no mouse required.",
        "body": "## Inbox navigation\n\n- `j` / `k` - next / previous conversation\n- `e` - resolve\n- `a` - assign to me\n- `s` - snooze\n\n## Composer\n\n- `Cmd+Enter` - send\n- `/` - open saved-reply picker\n- `Cmd+K` - command palette (everything)\n\n## Tip\n\nHover any button in the dashboard - the tooltip shows its shortcut."
      }
    },
